<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 05 at 8:58AM CDT  by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Limestone and northeastern Falls Counties through 930 AM CDT...
At 858 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Marlin, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Marlin, Groesbeck, Lake Limestone, Thornton, Kosse, Farrar, Oletha,
Fallon, Box Church, Reagan and McClanahan.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
